The forces of the mega strike are coming together
The unions of the League and the National Association of Workers' Councils will form, on Friday, their strike committee that will be responsible for coordinating the indefinite strike of Monday.
On Saturday, a general assembly of protest will be held and on Monday, the day of the final vote on the law on health funds, the strike will begin.
This action will certainly cause major traffic jams because the rail traffic will be almost completely stopped and the employees of BKV (public transport company) will also strike until 1pm.
The unions of the league will make known, Friday afternoon, the details of their strike on Monday, organized with the National Association of Workers' Councils.
The strike commission of LIGA - MOSZ will also be constituted, it will serve as coordinator of Monday's actions.
On Saturday, a general assembly of protests will be held and, starting Monday, the organizations joining the strike will stop work for an indefinite period if they fail to reach an agreement with the government.
This means that the date of the end of the strike, from the day of the vote in parliament on the Health Funds Act, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not pass the Health Insurance Act, the unions will immediately withdraw the call for strikes.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide what action to take.
According to the National Assembly's Monday agenda, it is likely that the vote on the Health Insurance Act will only take place late in the evening or even at night.
Due to the planned strike on Monday, major traffic stops are planned: the railways will stop work indefinitely and during the morning part of the public transport in Budapest and more than half of the Volán companies are at risk of being stopped.
At the same time, at different points in the country, half the way will also be blocked.
Many trade unions and civil organizations have joined the call for strikes, the list of them is constantly updated on the website of the League.
Some organizations report a strike indefinitely, others have declared a temporary stoppage of work.
Until Thursday afternoon the M<0xC3><0x81>V (Hungarian Railways) and the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ) failed to reach an agreement on minimum services, but, as the Christmas holidays approached, more and more people were taking the train.
According to current communications, public transport in Budapest will strike from the beginning of service until 1pm, Budapest airport between 7am and 9am, the Industrial Trade Unions of Electricity and Thermal Energy of the League will strike for four hours, the Teachers' Union and the Democratic Teachers' Union called for strike for 8 hours respectively at 2 hours and 2 hours.
The National Association of Physicians will strike across the country in alternation, the Union of Health and Social Sector Employees (EDDSZ) attached to the SZEF will strike a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands, formulated by the League, requires the government to withdraw its proposal on health reform and submit a new conception to the social debate.
The second claim requires that the new method of calculating retirement to be implemented from next year be introduced in several stages.
The third claim seeks a guarantee, in terms of retirement before the legal age, that would make it possible to pass through the system the functions that merit it before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ), attached to the Unions of the League, of the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport concerning the secondary railway lines and the waiting for another proposal.
Political Capital: The Hungarian Guard has increased country risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed last August, with the support of the Jobbik Magyarországért Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary), increases the political risk of Hungary and the region in several aspects.
In its “risk warning”, the company points out that, in connection with the Hungarian Guard’s activity, the greatest political risk is already that “in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes can occur as a result of the already existing ethnic tension between Hungary’s gypsy and non-gypsy population.”
The research institute added that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is likely to provoke this situation, is the main reason.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: “public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of radical and extreme political groups that have based a political strategy on the dispute between the Gypsies and the Hungarians.”
The problem gets worse, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and aggressive conflicts are more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, under the effect of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media, the activity of the Hungarian Guard "has significantly deteriorated Hungary's image abroad, in particular regarding confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country".
They recall that, following greater publicity given to the reorganization of Hungarian radical and extreme right-wing groups since the autumn of 2006, numerous associations have been formed in Hungary since the summer of 2007 giving themselves the name of "national self-defense association".
“The common trait of these gatherings is that they define themselves as a civilian organization as they publicly declare the preparation of their members for defense missions (catastrophes, national defense, defense of order), armed if necessary, in addition, evoking the incapacity of the police, the army, in other words of the state,” they added.
They pointed out that everything was going according to the method that, based on the resentment of the society of politics and parties, seeks to disguise different political ambitions under a civil aspect.
The emphasis on civil character and association status therefore serves only to avoid the legal pitfalls of registering these associations in court but they are also a political strategy.
