600,000 people failed to renew their driver’s license in time
Six hundred thousand drivers allowed the deadline to expire and failed to renew their old driver's license, which expires at the end of the year.
This is the last day that people can still apply for renewal, so the authorities will be able to issue them a new permit before the end of the year.
However, the Department is not afraid that hundreds of thousands of drivers without a valid licence will be on the road.
According to the authorities, they have not renewed their driving license especially those who no longer want to drive.
As municipalities report a drop in the number of licence renewal applications, authorities in the capital are inundated with applications and the number of licence renewal applications has increased this week.
The City Council satisfies about 2,000 customers per day.
There's a queue of about half an hour.
In Prague, nearly 140.OOO drivers have not yet renewed their driving licences.
The issuance of a new permit takes 20 days.
However, it is possible to apply for delivery within a shortened period of five days.
In this case, the driver pays an extra five hundred crowns.
Vehicle drivers who fail to renew their driver's licence by the end of the year and who will be on the road without a valid licence will face a fine from January onwards.
The culprit will be forced to pay a maximum of two thousand crowns.
However, the police officer may also deal with the offence through amicable proceedings.
In the case of an administrative offence, the fine rises to 2,500 kroner.
According to old information, even a person who was not going to circulate was liable to a fine.
In doing so, she could be forced to pay up to 30,000 crowns.
The Ministry had called on the authorities to moderate and impose fines not exceeding 1,000 kroner.
However, according to the spokesman of the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka, no one faces fines in the tens of thousands.
The driver's license, he said, is a document that people can decide whether or not they want to have it.
It is not as with the ID card, which must be valid without exceptions.
People who no longer want to drive should hand over their driver’s license.
Just bring it or send it to the corresponding municipality.
Driving licences issued between 1964 and 1993 will cease to be valid at the end of the year.
However, vehicle drivers are also forced to gradually renew other types of driving licences.
Persons with documents from 1994 to 2000 still have three years to complete the renewal.
The validity of driving licences issued in the years 2001 to 2004 expires in December 2013.
According to Hanzelka, these are about 2.6 million other documents.
