Which insurance is suitable for me?
Automobile insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible claims, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies determine their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the likelihood of an accident, the higher the rate to be paid.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower claim rate due to their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the probability of having an accident.
As the frequency increases, the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
This is why the driver must study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will explain the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various inconveniences when contracting with affordable insurance, such as low driving experience and seniority.
While the ideal for being well insured is risk-free insurance, other, more economical options exist.
The most forward-thinking drivers can opt for all-risk insurance with deductible, so that they get insurance coverage at all risks but at a more accessible price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the claim amount that the customer pays will be based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be lower," said Luis Noguera, the head of First Europa's Spain, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under 25 try to be cautious and avoid claims as much as possible, since this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
“The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it can afford to increase the bonuses, "clarifies Noguera.
After the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers to enter into a contract with insurance, since the loss rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is better to choose an all risk insurance with frankness.
“Normally young people cannot take advantage of the experience gained beforehand after an accident,” says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the ‘fear of the novice’ has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not have children yet, it is preferable that he negotiate insurance at all risks, as long as his economic situation allows him.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claim rate, because the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be a risk insurance with franchise (can be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have more casual driving and they have more purchasing power to afford the luxury of assuming a larger amount of franchises," Noguera said.
For retirees a risk-free insurance with deductible is preferable (with this being 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible claims, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is essential to study appropriately the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
